OL,3,CUse of chemotherapy and radiotherapy
OL,4,Cin UK 'lags behind other countries'
OL,6,FThe studies also found the average
OL,7,Ftime to start chemotherapy was 48 days
OL,8,Fin England, 65 in Scotland, 57 in
OL,9,FNorthern Ireland and 58 in Wales.
OL,11,FFor radiotherapy, the UK fared even
OL,12,Fworse, with it taking 63 days to start
OL,13,Ftreatment in England, 53 in Northern
OL,14,FIreland, 79 in Scotland and 81 in
OL,15,FWales.
OL,17,FCancer Research UK said delays to
OL,18,Fbegin treatment are partly the result
OL,19,Fof the UK Government's lack of long-
OL,20,Fterm planning on cancer in recent
OL,21,Fdecades.
